@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix snowkap: <http://snowkap.com/ontology/esg#> .

# =============================================================================
# Phase 24 (W5) — Layer 3 extension for the implicit ``_global`` tenant.
#
# This file is the per-tenant override surface. The ``_global`` tenant
# inherits all Layer 1 triples from data/ontology/{schema, knowledge_*,
# primitives_*, ...}.ttl WITHOUT any overrides, so this file stays empty
# and the pre-W5 behaviour is preserved bit-for-bit.
#
# When you onboard an external tenant (consulting firm, asset manager,
# in-house product), copy this file shape to
# data/ontology/tenants/<tenant_id>/extension.ttl and add tenant-specific
# triples — typically:
#
#   * MaterialityWeight overrides (a UK asset manager weights climate
#     risk differently than an Indian renewable consultancy)
#   * RegionalFrameworkBoost overrides (which frameworks the tenant
#     primarily reports against)
#   * MandatoryRule additions (tenant-specific compliance posture)
#   * HeadlineRule overrides (CFO word cap differs per tenant)
#   * StakeholderPosition additions (regulators / NGOs the tenant tracks)
#
# A future migration will EXTRACT the tenant-customisable triples that
# currently live in Layer 1 (knowledge_expansion.ttl) into per-tenant
# extension.ttl files. That work is deferred until the first external
# tenant lands and validates the resolver pattern in production. Today,
# this file is intentionally empty — the resolver loads it but it
# contributes zero triples.
# =============================================================================

# (intentionally empty)
